# Display

EasyGuard can display basic information on a status display.

[Source code](https://github.com/easyguard/ezgdisp)

Available as the `ezgdisp` package in the [EasyGuard Alpine repository](/docs/repo).

Supported displays are:
- AceMagic S1 Panel
- ðŸ”œ Turing Smart Screen

![Display](/img/display.png "Display")

## Data

The display shows data on both the left and right side.
- Left: Basic operation status information (goes red if check-engine was triggered)
- Right: Network interface information (2 interfaces, up/down speed, goes red if any interface is down)
